WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:03.537
Previously onThe Riches.
Bayou Hills.

00:03.604 --> 00:07.140
It's a hundred
and fifty million,
and you cash in on 13 million.

00:07.207 --> 00:10.476
‐ Thirteen million dollars?
‐ Deal closes,
we cash in, check out...

00:10.544 --> 00:12.112
<i>and adios,</i>
<i>just like any other con.</i>

00:12.178 --> 00:14.314
What did you do with Pete?
You killed him.

00:14.380 --> 00:16.449
‐ I hit him, but he fought back.
‐ You murdered him!

00:16.517 --> 00:19.285
No one's heard from Pete
since he left our place.

00:19.352 --> 00:24.791
You gave him that $40,000
that I buried and Sam found,
and he took it, right?

00:24.858 --> 00:27.761
Don't you
bullshit me, Wayne.

00:27.828 --> 00:31.765
Is Pete dead?
It was an accident.
No one meant for it to happen.

00:31.832 --> 00:34.968
I just think
if we could do one thing
that we know is true, Wayne.

00:35.035 --> 00:38.204
I'm Dahlia Malloy,
and I'm a parole violator.

00:38.271 --> 00:39.773
I'm doin' my best!

00:39.840 --> 00:41.842
But you're lyin' to me.
I'm lyin' a little bit.

00:41.908 --> 00:44.711
What about my parole? What are
you gonna do about my parole?
We're done!

00:44.778 --> 00:46.880
Hi.
Edenfalls Security.

00:46.947 --> 00:48.549
This is what
you do all day?

00:48.615 --> 00:50.751
I wanted to see you.

00:50.817 --> 00:54.087
‐ You're gonna run for mayor.
‐ Ta‐da! What do you think?

00:54.154 --> 00:57.724
Rather be piss‐poor with my dad
than $13 million richer
with whoever you are.

00:57.791 --> 00:59.993
‐ Where you headed, Cael?
‐ Just hittin' the road.

01:00.060 --> 01:01.361
[ Declan ]
This is Rosaleen.

01:01.427 --> 01:03.730
‐ Hi.
‐ Hi, Rosaleen.

01:03.797 --> 01:07.100
So what do you got for me?
I got Wayne Malloy wrapped
around my little finger.

01:07.167 --> 01:09.369
Bollocks.
[ Gasps ]

01:09.435 --> 01:11.572
Mr. Rich. I was just
wondering why I didn't the job.

01:13.640 --> 01:17.644
So you all know each other.
I get it.
It's a family project.

01:17.711 --> 01:20.413
This is bigger than me,
bigger than Reilly.

01:20.480 --> 01:22.849
I am asking you.
What are you scared of?

01:22.916 --> 01:25.185
[ Nina ]
I need to move Jim's birthday
party to your place tonight.

01:25.251 --> 01:27.588
First word.
First word.

01:27.654 --> 01:30.857
[ Laughing ]
"Fall to the Ground"?

01:30.924 --> 01:36.162
‐ Oh, Dead Calm!
‐ I can't hear his heartbeat!
Somebody call an ambulance!

01:37.097 --> 01:39.299
[ Alarm Clock Beeping ]

01:41.334 --> 01:45.271
<i>[ Sam ] Dad, wake up.</i>
<i>You're gonna be late</i>
<i>for the funeral.</i>

01:45.338 --> 01:47.473
Okay. Okay, okay.

01:47.541 --> 01:49.976
<i>[ Man On TV, Indistinct ]</i>

01:50.043 --> 01:52.713
[ Turns Off ]
[ Sighs ]

01:52.779 --> 01:55.982
Don't worry, Sammi.
It's gonna be okay.
It's all gonna be okay.

01:56.049 --> 01:58.151
Dad, it's 8:30.
We're gonna be late.

01:58.218 --> 01:59.553
8:30?
Yeah.

01:59.620 --> 02:01.588
Morning.

02:14.901 --> 02:17.704
Dale's truck has been
parked outside
for three days now.

02:17.771 --> 02:19.706
Where the hell
do you think he could be?

02:19.773 --> 02:21.708
Sam, you're gonna
be late for the bus.

02:21.775 --> 02:24.911
Di Di?
I'll be waitin' in the car.
<i>Hmm?</i>

02:35.321 --> 02:37.758
Who knew Jim
had so many friends?

02:42.529 --> 02:44.798
<i>[ Wayne ]</i>
<i>Dahlia?</i>

02:46.232 --> 02:48.134
Dahlia.

02:48.201 --> 02:50.771
[ Car Alarm Chirps ]
Damn it, Dahlia.
I'm talking to you.

02:50.837 --> 02:53.607
This is not the gulag.
I don't deserve
this silent bullshit.

02:55.075 --> 02:58.211
Look, everything I have done,
I have done for this family.

02:58.278 --> 02:59.713
That's the lie you like
to tell yourself.

02:59.780 --> 03:01.748
Goddamn it.
Would you two just stop it?

03:01.815 --> 03:04.618
‐ What the hell is goin' on?
‐ Ask your father.

03:04.685 --> 03:07.954
<i>I'm askin' both of you.</i>
<i>Is it about Cael?</i>

03:09.523 --> 03:12.458
‐ No. No, it's nothing.
‐ Bullshit.

03:12.526 --> 03:14.795
We're talking about Pete, Di Di.

03:14.861 --> 03:16.930
Ask your father
what happened to Pete.

03:18.198 --> 03:21.234
‐ Jesus, Dahlia.
‐ Pete?

03:21.301 --> 03:23.504
What happened to Pete?

03:23.570 --> 03:26.673
‐ <i>Daddy?</i>
‐ <i>[ Cell Phone Rings ]</i>

03:26.740 --> 03:28.775
‐ Dad!
‐ <i>[ Cell Phone Beeps ]</i>

03:28.842 --> 03:31.377
Okay.

03:31.444 --> 03:34.548
[ Sighs ]
Pete died.

03:35.516 --> 03:37.450
What?
It was an accident.

03:37.518 --> 03:39.485
‐ He's dead?
‐ Yeah, Pete's dead.

03:39.553 --> 03:42.856
<i>Dale killed him,</i>
<i>and your dad buried him.</i>

03:44.357 --> 03:46.259
[ Scoffs ]

03:46.326 --> 03:48.962
Baby, I am‐‐
[ Sighs ]

04:09.115 --> 04:12.418
[ Wes ]
My Jim was a man
of many, many talents.

04:12.485 --> 04:16.723
He discovered his...
passion late in life.

04:16.790 --> 04:19.091
[ Nickers ]
But when he did,
he committed to it...

04:19.159 --> 04:21.060
with all his heart and soul.

04:21.127 --> 04:23.730
There are no words
to describe my love‐‐
Sorry.

04:23.797 --> 04:26.933
for this fine man.

04:27.000 --> 04:29.936
<i>But I would be doing him</i>
<i>a great disservice</i>
<i>were I not to mention...</i>

04:30.003 --> 04:32.272
the generosity of spirit,

04:32.338 --> 04:34.541
the exemplary
Christian forgiveness...

04:34.608 --> 04:37.343
that Nina
has shown to both of us.

04:39.345 --> 04:43.149
Nina, would you like
to say a few words?
<i>[ Cell Phone Rings ]</i>

04:43.216 --> 04:45.819
[ Man ]
Oh, come on.
<i>[ Ringing ]</i>

04:45.886 --> 04:49.355
[ Beeps ]
Um‐‐

04:51.191 --> 04:53.193
Uh,

04:53.259 --> 04:56.362
I was married to Jim for‐‐

04:58.198 --> 05:00.233
for 25 years.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.302
And I'm sure
most of you are wondering...

05:02.368 --> 05:06.507
how I could be married
to a gay man for that long
without knowing it.

05:10.877 --> 05:12.646
Well, guess what.

05:13.647 --> 05:16.382
It's none
of your goddamn business.

05:16.449 --> 05:18.852
‐ Nina.
‐ Friends?

05:18.919 --> 05:20.587
<i>Amongst friends?</i>

05:20.654 --> 05:22.556
I don't know any of you people.

05:22.623 --> 05:24.591
If this whole thing
had been up to me,

05:24.658 --> 05:27.528
Jim would have been cremated
and stuck in a closet somewhere.

05:27.594 --> 05:29.863
Do you think
I would have had any of this?

05:29.930 --> 05:33.700
I hate funerals!
[ Sobbing ]
I hate funerals!

05:33.767 --> 05:36.302
I hate that goddamn alpaca!

05:36.369 --> 05:39.540
And I really hate all of you!

05:39.606 --> 05:42.843
[ Sobbing ]
[ Dahlia ] Okay, sweetheart.
Come on. Gonna get outta here.

05:42.909 --> 05:45.512
Come on. Come on.

05:45.579 --> 05:47.748
Okay.
Come on.

05:47.814 --> 05:50.517
Let's go.
[ Nina Sobbing ]
Take me away from here.

05:50.584 --> 05:53.119
Far away from here
as humanly possible.

05:55.455 --> 05:58.124
[ Rosaleen ]
"Like a bit of stone,
I lie under a broken tree."

06:00.226 --> 06:01.862
What?

06:01.928 --> 06:06.466
"I could recover if I shrieked
my heart's agony...

06:08.201 --> 06:11.738
"to passing bird,

06:11.805 --> 06:13.707
but I am dumb
from human dignity."

06:13.774 --> 06:15.676
What's that supposed to mean?

06:15.742 --> 06:18.812
I'm not sure.
[ Chuckling ]

06:18.879 --> 06:20.446
<i>It's from a book</i>
<i>that Quinn loaned me.</i>

06:20.514 --> 06:23.083
I liked the way it sounded.

06:24.484 --> 06:27.220
Especially the...

06:27.287 --> 06:29.990
"shrieking
my heart's agony" part.

06:32.526 --> 06:34.928
What do you think it means?

06:34.995 --> 06:37.130
It should mean
whatever you want it to.

06:40.233 --> 06:43.136
I want it to mean
someone thinks I'm smart enough
to figure it out.

06:46.707 --> 06:49.042
And I'm not just
some dumb trailer trash.

06:53.814 --> 06:56.016
You're not.

07:03.323 --> 07:06.159
♪♪♪♪ [ Bagpipes: "Amazing Grace" ]

07:15.769 --> 07:18.471
Is it true?
Baby‐‐

07:18.539 --> 07:20.641
So this is who we are?

07:20.707 --> 07:22.776
<i>[ Cell Phone Buzzing ]</i>

07:25.646 --> 07:28.414
‐ [ Sighs ]
‐ Di Di. Di Di.

07:28.481 --> 07:30.216
[ Beeps ]
What?

07:30.283 --> 07:33.554
Where the hell you at, Doug?
Get your ass down here.
I mean yesterday.

07:33.620 --> 07:36.590
‐ Down where?
‐ Bayou Hills construction site.
Where the hell do you think?

07:36.657 --> 07:39.660
Got a shit storm goin' on
down here. You're not answering
your goddamn phone?

07:39.726 --> 07:41.828
I'll be right there.
Di Di?

07:44.364 --> 07:49.069
[ Sighs ]
Crap.

07:51.237 --> 07:54.641
♪♪♪♪ [ Latin, Muffled ]

07:56.076 --> 07:58.211
No. Go on, Jimmy.
Come on.
This is my neighbor.

07:58.278 --> 08:00.213
Come on.

08:06.653 --> 08:10.524
This your place?
Oh, yeah.

08:10.591 --> 08:12.893
It's uh‐‐ It's complicated.

08:12.959 --> 08:16.296
It's kinda like
my secret getaway...

08:16.362 --> 08:19.465
where I get to be alone.

08:19.533 --> 08:22.002
Hey, you want some coffee?

08:22.068 --> 08:23.937
Somethin'?

08:24.004 --> 08:26.573
No one else know
about this place?
Nope.

08:28.542 --> 08:30.711
‐ Not even Wayne?
‐ Especially not Wayne.

08:34.246 --> 08:36.282
Coffee all you got?

08:36.349 --> 08:38.885
[ Groaning ]

08:42.422 --> 08:45.592
[ Groaning Continues ]

08:45.659 --> 08:47.861
[ Man ] What happened?
[ Paramedic ]
Pretty good shape, considering.

08:54.935 --> 08:57.237
Jesus Christ!
What happened here?
Chain broke.

08:57.303 --> 08:59.640
Poor bastard
may never walk again.
<i>Don't say that.</i>

08:59.706 --> 09:01.542
You don't know that.
Where the hell you been?

09:01.608 --> 09:05.445
‐ I was at a funeral.
‐ <i>Aw, I'm not that good</i>
<i>with blood.</i>

09:05.512 --> 09:07.848
Hang in there, buddy.

09:07.914 --> 09:10.517
I'm gonna do everything I can.
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>

09:10.584 --> 09:13.954
‐ Get you anything you need.
‐ You don't look so good.
Why don't you sit down?

09:14.020 --> 09:16.890
‐ Aw, I'm fine.
‐ No, I don't think so.

09:16.957 --> 09:19.359
Come on.

09:19.425 --> 09:21.828
How does this happen to me?

09:21.895 --> 09:23.830
Put your head
between your legs.

09:23.897 --> 09:27.901
Okay. All right.
Oh.
All righty?

09:27.968 --> 09:31.638
‐ [ Man Grunts ]
‐ How could that
goddamn chain break?

09:32.806 --> 09:36.109
<i>I mean, what are the odds</i>
<i>on that, Doug?</i>

09:36.176 --> 09:38.879
How many tons of crap
does that thing
lift in its lifetime?

09:38.945 --> 09:42.516
Decides to go and break on me?
Maybe this is it.

09:42.583 --> 09:45.018
This? This is what?

09:45.085 --> 09:48.589
Karma... finally
bitin' me in the ass.

09:48.655 --> 09:51.525
Man seriously injured
on my watch.

09:51.592 --> 09:53.694
You know, Gi Gi‐‐ Gi Gi‐‐

09:53.760 --> 09:55.729
she says
you create your own luck.

09:55.796 --> 09:59.065
What are you talkin' about here?
This was an accident. Yeah?
Yeah.

09:59.132 --> 10:02.803
Accidents happen.
We can't control everything.
We're not God.

10:02.869 --> 10:06.707
Let me tell you somethin'.
I've been a contractor 21 years.

10:07.741 --> 10:09.610
This was no goddamn accident.

10:09.676 --> 10:12.212
[ Man Grunting ]

10:17.884 --> 10:20.854
‐ Well, I guess I made a lot
of friends back there, huh?
‐ Tough shit.

10:20.921 --> 10:23.423
You're allowed to feel like crap
at your husband's funeral.

10:23.489 --> 10:25.291
You know?

10:25.358 --> 10:29.329
<i>Even if you weren't</i>
<i>exactly... together.</i>

10:30.631 --> 10:32.833
You know what I mean?

10:34.267 --> 10:36.136
I did love him.

10:36.202 --> 10:38.238
I know you did.

10:38.304 --> 10:41.241
[ Cell Phone Beeps ]
Hey, hold on one sec. Just‐‐

10:42.809 --> 10:45.746
<i>[ Wayne On Phone ]</i>
<i>Dahlia, I think</i>
<i>you should call me.</i>

10:45.812 --> 10:49.282
Bastard.
Problems at home?

10:53.486 --> 10:56.356
No.
It's my parole officer.

10:56.422 --> 11:00.126
[ Scoffs ]
Your parole officer?

11:01.461 --> 11:03.997
Welcome to my double life, Nina.

11:07.033 --> 11:10.504
Wilkinson quit.
Shit.

11:10.571 --> 11:12.639
Says his crew
doesn't feel safe.

11:12.706 --> 11:15.676
Our insurance company finds out
this might have been foul play,

11:15.742 --> 11:18.244
the whole damn project's
in the shitter.

11:18.311 --> 11:20.213
Countin' on you here, Doug.
I appreciate that.

11:20.280 --> 11:22.248
No more goddamn
surprise funerals, okay?

11:22.315 --> 11:24.384
Drink your water.
It's good for the shock.

11:24.450 --> 11:27.320
You gotta start gettin'
your head in the right place
for our campaign announcement,

11:27.387 --> 11:31.357
'cause you winning this election
is vital to the success
of Bayou Hills.

11:31.424 --> 11:33.426
Mmm.

11:34.761 --> 11:39.132
Doug, you really think
I can win this thing?

11:39.199 --> 11:41.902
[ Alarm Chiming ]
Absolutely.

11:41.968 --> 11:44.037
Hugh Panetta can win
whatever he goddamn pleases.

11:47.373 --> 11:49.510
‐ You better believe it.
‐ Remember that.

11:49.576 --> 11:52.579
[ Cell Phone Beeps ]
Aubrey, it's me.

11:52.646 --> 11:54.515
There's been a change of plans.

11:54.581 --> 11:58.552
Okay. I want you
to get Berthaud Construction
in the office,

11:58.619 --> 12:00.554
and I want you
to phone Felix Minkov.

12:00.621 --> 12:04.758
Tell him I want to see him.
All right.

12:04.825 --> 12:08.494
So you're an ex‐con?
And a drug addict.

12:08.562 --> 12:10.831
Don't forget that part.

12:10.897 --> 12:13.634
And a parole violator.

12:13.700 --> 12:16.236
Yeah, I got lost.

12:16.302 --> 12:18.805
Got badly lost.

12:20.173 --> 12:22.809
Then I turned into
someone else.

12:22.876 --> 12:25.145
Cherien Rich.
No, I mean in here.

12:25.211 --> 12:27.247
I turned into
someone else in here.

12:27.313 --> 12:30.250
I just gotta keep
giving myself
a second chance, you know?

12:30.316 --> 12:33.554
I blew it
with this parole officer.

12:33.620 --> 12:36.890
I‐‐ And I don't know
what to do.

12:36.957 --> 12:39.660
There's probably
a warrant out for my arrest.

12:39.726 --> 12:42.095
[ Scoffs ]

12:42.162 --> 12:44.364
You are so
full of shit, Dahlia.

12:45.866 --> 12:48.101
We just came from
my husband's funeral.

12:49.603 --> 12:53.574
My husband's funeral.

12:53.640 --> 12:54.741
Sorry.
I'm sorry.

12:54.808 --> 12:56.510
Oh, shut up!

12:58.478 --> 13:02.182
I'm not done with you.
But I am done with the lies.

13:02.248 --> 13:05.519
Dahlia, you couldn't
tell the truth...

13:05.586 --> 13:07.988
if your life
depended on it.

13:13.359 --> 13:15.862
Well, it does
depend on it, Nina.

13:22.035 --> 13:24.871
Come here.
I'm sorry.

13:27.207 --> 13:29.676
[ Sighs ]

13:29.743 --> 13:33.346
Yes. Well,

13:33.413 --> 13:36.182
answer this for me.

13:38.819 --> 13:42.956
What's the story
on the P. I....

13:43.023 --> 13:45.892
who came to my house
the other day...

13:45.959 --> 13:48.294
asking about that guy Pete?

14:00.273 --> 14:02.576
I don't know
what happened to Pete.

14:08.281 --> 14:11.051
[ Sighs ]

14:15.088 --> 14:17.924
I was Jim's beard
for 25 years.

14:17.991 --> 14:20.060
I knew he was gay...

14:20.126 --> 14:22.162
while I lied to myself‐‐

14:22.228 --> 14:25.899
to everyone‐‐
all those years.

14:25.966 --> 14:28.935
You want to give yourself
a second chance?

14:29.002 --> 14:31.337
You want to be my friend?

14:33.707 --> 14:36.943
Then face the truth.

14:39.780 --> 14:41.582
I don't know
what the truth is, Nina.

14:41.648 --> 14:43.617
Oh!

14:43.684 --> 14:46.319
[ Sniffles ]

14:46.386 --> 14:49.255
I gotta go home
and scrounge myself up a joint.

14:49.322 --> 14:53.727
This day has been for shit!

14:53.794 --> 14:56.229
[ Door Slams ]

15:01.334 --> 15:04.738
[ Man On Walkie‐talkie ]
Zero Alpha One, get a gosh‐darn
grip on your radio procedure.

15:04.805 --> 15:07.373
[ Walkie‐talkie Beeps ]
Right. Sorry.

15:07.440 --> 15:11.344
When I say "radio check,"
you say, "Copy. Over." Over.

15:14.748 --> 15:15.982
Hi.

15:16.049 --> 15:18.118
<i>"Copy. Over."</i>

15:20.821 --> 15:23.890
Zero Alpha One,
acknowledge my last‐‐
[ Static ]

15:23.957 --> 15:27.260
Over.
Uh‐‐

15:27.327 --> 15:29.395
Mmm? What?

15:39.172 --> 15:41.808
Copy. Over.
Mmm, copy. Over.

15:41.875 --> 15:44.578
I know. I know.
It's just‐‐
Oops.

15:44.645 --> 15:47.280
Come in. Over.

15:48.414 --> 15:50.450
Snooze, you lose, Ike.
Copy. Over.

15:50.517 --> 15:52.686
Di Di.

15:52.753 --> 15:54.888
[ Chuckles ]

15:54.955 --> 15:57.457
Are they home?
I don't know.

15:57.524 --> 16:00.527
Are they home?
Are they home?
Find out.

16:00.594 --> 16:04.531
Dahlia, what do I have to do
to get you to answer my calls?

16:04.598 --> 16:07.233
I mean, what can I say?
What do you want me to do?

16:07.300 --> 16:10.070
Please, call me back.
[ Beeps ]

16:10.136 --> 16:12.939
What other issues are you
concerned with, Mr. Panetta?
Thirteen million. Jesus Christ.

16:13.006 --> 16:15.408
<i>[ Chuckling ]</i>
<i>I love it when</i>
<i>you call me Mr. Panetta.</i>

16:15.475 --> 16:17.410
Mr. Panetta.
You bonin' up
for the news conference?

16:17.477 --> 16:20.046
I'm all over it, Doug.
You're a natural, baby.

16:20.113 --> 16:22.716
Hey, hey.
How'd it go after I left?

16:22.783 --> 16:26.119
Well, the guy's gonna make it,
but we gotta change contractors.
Berthaud's on his way in.

16:26.186 --> 16:29.856
‐ [ Sighs ]
‐ And you will be wearing this.

16:29.923 --> 16:31.758
What's this?
Shut up.
Just wear it.

16:31.825 --> 16:33.660
Now, Jackie O.

16:33.727 --> 16:37.030
‐ I don't think
this is really me.
‐ Trust me.

16:37.097 --> 16:39.900
‐ And we got you
a new résumé as well.
‐ No, no. It's, uh‐‐

16:39.966 --> 16:42.468
You have a background
in women's issues,
arts, education.

16:42.536 --> 16:45.205
‐ I do teach pole dancin'.
‐ Well, there you go.

16:45.271 --> 16:48.274
<i>And now you'll be going by</i>
<i>your given name, "Georgia."</i>
<i>Okay?</i>

16:48.341 --> 16:51.111
‐ Okay.
‐ That's my Turd Blossom.
That's what I call him.

16:51.177 --> 16:54.080
It's kinda scary.
Georgia?

16:54.147 --> 16:56.216
Mr. Panetta.
Ooh, Georgia, come here.

17:01.221 --> 17:03.123
Are you kiddin'‐‐ Look‐‐

17:03.189 --> 17:05.892
Look at this place.

17:05.959 --> 17:08.194
[ Scoffs ]

17:08.261 --> 17:11.364
I mean, wh‐who would
actually, like,
want to live here?

17:13.465 --> 17:15.300
[ Sighs ]

17:15.367 --> 17:17.738
Do you think
maybe this isn't the best idea?

17:17.804 --> 17:21.241
You said they're in Gulfport
for the weekend, didn't you?

17:21.307 --> 17:24.243
Yeah.
Fantastic.
Then relax a little bit.

17:24.310 --> 17:27.380
Live a little.
Cheers.

17:27.446 --> 17:29.382
Cheers.

17:33.687 --> 17:38.692
[ Coughs, Clears Throat ]
God, my feet are killing me.

17:38.759 --> 17:41.895
Are you sure your boss
is out of the picture?
Yeah. Four hours minimum.

17:41.962 --> 17:43.697
Yeah?
Cameras are down in sector 14.

17:45.198 --> 17:47.400
Sector 14?
[ Laughs ]

17:47.467 --> 17:49.603
Shit. How many
sectors are there?

17:49.670 --> 17:52.472
Oh, God.
I don't know.
He keeps adding them.

17:52.539 --> 17:54.875
Yeah, I bet he does.
He's kind of a fanatic.

17:54.941 --> 17:57.678
[ Sighs ]
Chairs are kinda bouncy.

18:00.647 --> 18:03.449
Oh, come on.

18:03.517 --> 18:05.552
What are you
so worked up about, huh?

18:21.802 --> 18:22.903
I'm redecorating.

18:22.969 --> 18:24.605
[ Clearing Throat ]

18:24.671 --> 18:29.009
Your opponent, Carol Phipps,
committed environmentalist
and barracuda...

18:29.075 --> 18:31.512
when unleashed
upon corporate America.

18:31.578 --> 18:33.814
Uh, can I just quit now?
Hey.

18:33.880 --> 18:36.216
Oh, I'm kiddin'. I'm kiddin'.
Just kiddin', baby.

18:36.282 --> 18:38.719
Now, after this
press conference, which
you will keep short and sweet,

18:38.785 --> 18:40.954
you hit the bricks, getting
to know the electorate,

18:41.021 --> 18:42.923
while we put together
the ad campaign.

18:42.989 --> 18:47.260
Then a fund‐raiser at
the country club, photo op at
the V. A., Rotary Club debate.

18:47.327 --> 18:49.162
Remember,
one sound bite at a time.

18:49.229 --> 18:52.365
You are really
into this shit, Doug.
It is‐‐ It is kinda scary.

18:52.432 --> 18:55.001
Very Jackie O.
I like it. Ready?

18:55.068 --> 18:56.837
Hugh Panetta was born ready.
Bring it on.

18:56.903 --> 18:58.639
[ Sighs ]

18:58.705 --> 19:02.543
Ladies and gentlemen,
the next mayor of Ducaine,
Mr. Hugh Panetta.

19:02.609 --> 19:05.045
How y'all doin'?
Yeah. How are ya?

19:05.111 --> 19:07.714
‐ <i>[ Scattered Applause ]</i>
‐ <i>Hey. Thanks for comin' out.</i>

19:07.781 --> 19:11.251
Hey, how you been?
How are you today?
Good.

19:11.317 --> 19:13.219
Nice to see you.
God bless America.

19:13.286 --> 19:14.755
Thanks for comin' out.

19:14.821 --> 19:17.157
Why, uh‐‐ Why, uh,
just the other day‐‐
Afternoon, Mister Rich.

19:17.223 --> 19:19.225
Dan Berthaud,
Berthaud Construction.

19:19.292 --> 19:21.061
Thank you for coming.
I'm sorry the situation‐‐

19:21.127 --> 19:24.965
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]
Oh, excuse me.
I have to take this.

19:25.031 --> 19:27.067
Joe Reilly here, Doug.

19:27.133 --> 19:29.770
I'm just calling to
let you know that now that
Wilkinson has quit,

19:29.836 --> 19:32.506
I'm gonna be startin' work
as your new contractor.

19:33.674 --> 19:37.410
Me and me men are down here now.
Doug, you there?

19:37.477 --> 19:40.013
Yeah.

19:40.080 --> 19:42.616
Yeah, I'm still here.
[ Beeps ]

19:42.683 --> 19:46.252
...kind of business that once
made this country of ours great.

19:46.319 --> 19:48.288
Good, old‐fashioned,
regular, everyday,

19:48.354 --> 19:51.024
"How you doin', Mrs. Wilson‐‐

19:51.091 --> 19:53.727
"Great to see‐‐
My, what a nice hat,

19:53.794 --> 19:56.930
how's the family"
kind of business, huh?

19:56.997 --> 20:00.100
[ Man ]
How do you plan to
accomplish that, Mr. Panetta?

20:00.166 --> 20:03.970
Politics is about solutions,
not problems.

20:04.037 --> 20:05.371
American politics.

20:05.438 --> 20:09.576
Pure, 100% bullshit.

20:09.643 --> 20:11.712
Best bullshitter
always wins.

20:11.778 --> 20:13.246
Got your message.

20:13.313 --> 20:17.183
So I have two words for Ducaine.
One, tourism.

20:17.250 --> 20:21.788
So, I scratch my back,
you scratch yours?

20:21.855 --> 20:23.857
Yes.

20:23.924 --> 20:26.192
Two, construction.

20:26.259 --> 20:30.196
Although in America,
it's you scratch my back,
I'll scratch yours.

20:30.263 --> 20:32.332
We live in a great town.

20:32.398 --> 20:34.334
We have great people.

20:34.400 --> 20:36.870
You know what I mean.

20:36.937 --> 20:39.906
With regards to?

20:39.973 --> 20:42.743
With regards to
the next mayor of Ducaine.

20:42.809 --> 20:45.679
It's time to make
the most of Ducaine.

20:45.746 --> 20:48.582
You want me to stab
my partner in the back.

20:49.783 --> 20:52.052
Out with the old,

20:52.118 --> 20:54.120
in with the Hugh.
[ Applause ]

20:54.187 --> 20:56.623
Oh, yeah.

20:56.690 --> 20:59.793
Isn't that American business?

20:59.860 --> 21:01.628
Come here, gorgeous.

21:01.695 --> 21:03.664
That was great.
Thank you.

21:03.730 --> 21:05.498
You're a natural.
[ Laughs ]

21:05.566 --> 21:08.334
And this is
my lovely wife, Georgia.

21:15.008 --> 21:17.343
Hey.

21:18.512 --> 21:20.380
You're done now, Reilly.
You can go.

21:20.446 --> 21:23.016
[ Chuckling ]

21:24.651 --> 21:26.352
It is.
It's very funny.

21:26.419 --> 21:28.522
Thank you.

21:28.589 --> 21:32.225
I just want to be
seated for this.

21:32.292 --> 21:35.328
Comfortable?
Good.

21:35.395 --> 21:38.031
Gentlemen‐‐

21:38.098 --> 21:40.801
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

21:40.867 --> 21:43.036
[ Speaking Russian ]

21:50.043 --> 21:52.779
That's "Get out.
And you got three seconds."

21:54.047 --> 21:56.382
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

21:58.018 --> 22:01.021
Sounds much meaner
in Russian, doesn't it?

22:01.087 --> 22:04.791
I'd haul ass if I were you.
They don't speak much English.

22:08.128 --> 22:10.063
[ Chuckles ]

22:11.565 --> 22:15.168
You have no idea
who you're dealing with, Wayne.

22:15.235 --> 22:19.072
Do svidaniya, Reilly.

22:27.881 --> 22:31.084
<i>[ Russian ]</i>

22:37.190 --> 22:40.493
Oh, my gosh. So there's
this, like, totally cute top
at the mall the other day.

22:40.561 --> 22:45.431
And I told my mom, and it was
really cute, and, um‐‐

22:45.498 --> 22:49.202
Well, I guess it doesn't matter.
I'll probably get it
as a gift or something.

22:49.269 --> 22:52.005
I mean, I don't know.
But it was really, really cute.

22:55.942 --> 22:59.846
And the security
is 24‐7, correct?
Absolutely.

23:03.584 --> 23:06.119
You can start now.
You got it.

23:08.388 --> 23:10.591
Cael, darlin', it's your mother.

23:10.657 --> 23:13.226
Oh, I miss you so much.

23:13.293 --> 23:16.396
Will you come home, baby?
Please? Will you come home?

23:20.233 --> 23:22.035
[ Sniffles ]
Okay.

23:26.740 --> 23:30.176
[ Men Grunting ]
[ Blows Landing ]

23:30.243 --> 23:32.613
[ Grunting Continues ]

23:36.983 --> 23:39.252
Come with me.

23:39.319 --> 23:42.623
Or don't come.
I won't ask twice.

23:45.025 --> 23:46.927
[ Grunting ]

23:46.993 --> 23:48.762
[ Shouts ]

23:57.170 --> 24:01.341
♪♪ But though the tempest
round me roars ♪♪

24:01.407 --> 24:05.779
♪♪ I feel the truth
it liveth ♪♪

24:07.514 --> 24:09.916
[ Both Grunting ]

24:13.053 --> 24:14.788
[ Man ]
Oh, man!

24:15.989 --> 24:17.290
[ Grunts ]

24:17.357 --> 24:21.094
♪♪ It sounds and echoes ♪♪

24:21.161 --> 24:23.129
♪♪ Through my soul ♪♪

24:23.196 --> 24:25.065
[ Grunting ]

24:27.568 --> 24:30.671
The knife.
Take the knife.
Take the knife.

24:32.606 --> 24:35.408
♪♪ Songs in the night ♪♪

24:35.475 --> 24:37.511
♪♪ It giveth ♪♪

24:37.578 --> 24:41.181
Get up.
Back off.

24:41.247 --> 24:43.349
Your beef's over, fellas.

24:43.416 --> 24:47.521
Because gone are the days that
we Travellers destroy each other
with our petty feuds.

24:47.588 --> 24:52.092
♪♪ No storm can shake
my inmost calm ♪♪

24:52.158 --> 24:57.363
We are the descendants
of Michael Collins,
Éamon de Valera.

24:57.430 --> 25:01.602
♪♪ I hear the music ringing ♪♪

25:01.668 --> 25:04.838
Take the Malloys.

25:04.905 --> 25:06.973
Who would ever
have thought it, huh?

25:08.008 --> 25:11.745
A Malloy standing
side by side with me...

25:11.812 --> 25:14.180
as an example
to the rest of us.

25:14.247 --> 25:19.586
♪♪ Love is lord
of heaven and earth ♪♪

25:23.423 --> 25:24.725
To the future.

25:25.959 --> 25:28.562
The future.

25:28.629 --> 25:31.197
‐ [ Woman ] Whoa.
‐ [ Man ]
I'll drink to that one.

25:31.264 --> 25:33.634
Sláinte.
Sláinte.

25:36.369 --> 25:39.640
♪♪ Can I keep ♪♪

25:39.706 --> 25:43.143
♪♪ From singing ♪♪♪♪

25:47.413 --> 25:49.816
Come on! Hey!
Let's have a song.

25:49.883 --> 25:52.185
[ Laughter ]
Can I have
my knife back now?

25:52.252 --> 25:55.789
♪♪♪♪ [ Folk ]

25:56.823 --> 26:00.694
No.
[ Laughing ]

26:00.761 --> 26:04.898
Come on now.
Hey, give us another drink.

26:04.965 --> 26:07.200
Bad boy.

26:07.267 --> 26:11.304
[ Laughing ]
Oh. Shit. Isn't that one
of the guys on my school board?

26:11.371 --> 26:13.339
Oh, my God.
I don't know.

26:13.406 --> 26:16.843
But I do know that she is
a real pain in the ass.

26:16.910 --> 26:20.614
Always complaining
about flyers in her mailbox.

26:20.681 --> 26:22.616
Buffer assholes.

26:22.683 --> 26:24.250
What's a buffer?

26:24.317 --> 26:26.419
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>Are you sorry? Take that.</i>

26:26.486 --> 26:28.321
Oh, just‐‐
It's just a word.

26:30.423 --> 26:34.327
[ Chuckles ]
Someone who consumes everything
in the entire world...

26:34.394 --> 26:36.229
and gives nothing back?

26:38.832 --> 26:42.368
Now that's
the American dream, honey.
Don't knock that.

26:42.435 --> 26:44.838
[ Both Grunting ]

26:44.905 --> 26:48.374
I don't believe
it has to be like this,
you know?

26:51.011 --> 26:54.214
Yeah. Well, that's 'cause
you're still a romantic.

26:56.449 --> 26:59.820
Yeah, I guess.

27:02.322 --> 27:04.224
Lucky you.

27:08.795 --> 27:10.797
Wait. Wait.
[ Scoffs ]

27:10.864 --> 27:13.166
Um‐‐ Uh‐‐
Uh‐‐

27:13.233 --> 27:15.435
Shit, I can't.
I‐‐ I‐‐ There's no way.

27:15.501 --> 27:18.204
[ Chuckles ]

27:18.271 --> 27:21.374
‐ Yeah, you're done.
‐ Yeah, that's better.

27:32.519 --> 27:34.721
[ Gi Gi ]
Mr. Big.

27:36.557 --> 27:39.626
[ Hugh Moaning ]
Oh, Gi Gi.

27:39.693 --> 27:42.262
Oh.
Call me Georgia.
Georgia, baby.

27:42.328 --> 27:43.964
Georgia.
Mmm.
Yeah.

27:44.030 --> 27:47.668
Talk politics to me, Mr. Mayor.
Talk politics. Come on, baby.

27:47.734 --> 27:49.636
<i>I stand before you‐‐</i>
<i>Oh, yeah!</i>

27:49.703 --> 27:51.972
<i>people of Ducaine!</i>
<i>Yeah!</i>

27:52.038 --> 27:54.240
<i>Oh!</i>
<i>Yeah, baby!</i>
<i>Don't stop!</i>

27:54.307 --> 27:56.142
<i>[ Both Moaning ]</i>

28:12.859 --> 28:16.429
[ Moaning Continues ]

28:17.698 --> 28:21.167
Who have you been visiting
in prison, Dale?

28:22.569 --> 28:24.871
And where are you now?

28:28.909 --> 28:32.746
‐ What you doin', buddy?
‐ Jesus Christ!

28:32.813 --> 28:34.480
You scared
the shit out of me.

28:34.548 --> 28:36.116
[ Chuckling ]
Ah.

28:36.182 --> 28:39.052
I'm up here
burning the midnight oil.

28:40.053 --> 28:42.255
At the mail boy's desk?

28:42.322 --> 28:46.860
[ Clears Throat ]
I‐‐ I gotta talk to you.

28:46.927 --> 28:49.696
I need to tell you somethin',
man‐to‐man.

28:49.763 --> 28:51.965
Yeah.

28:53.667 --> 28:57.003
Thank you, Doug.

28:57.070 --> 29:00.741
I won't forget
what you have done...

29:00.807 --> 29:02.943
and what you continue
to do for me.

29:07.948 --> 29:11.017
All right.
Good night, Turd Blossom.

29:11.084 --> 29:14.287
Yeah.
Good night.

29:17.190 --> 29:18.959
[ Sighs ]

29:19.025 --> 29:21.562
Thirteen million.

29:21.628 --> 29:23.463
My thirteen million.

29:23.530 --> 29:26.032
I fly to thee,
O Virgin of virgins, my Mother.

29:26.099 --> 29:28.334
I come to thee, and before thee
I stand sinful and sorrowful.

29:28.401 --> 29:33.073
O Mother of the World Incarnate,
despise not my petitions, but in
thy mercy hear and answer them.

29:33.139 --> 29:35.108
Amen.

29:42.315 --> 29:44.150
[ Sniffles ]

29:49.523 --> 29:51.391
[ Line Ringing ]

29:51.457 --> 29:55.028
This is Maurice Devereux.
Leave a message.
[ Beeps ]

29:55.095 --> 29:57.297
Yes, hello.
This is Dahlia.

29:58.364 --> 30:01.602
Uh, I really need
to talk to you, please.

30:01.668 --> 30:05.171
I've been trying for days now,
and I know you're pissed,
and you have every right to be,

30:05.238 --> 30:07.974
but if you could please
just call me back...

30:08.041 --> 30:11.144
and we could talk...
honestly...

30:13.680 --> 30:15.816
about everything.

30:15.882 --> 30:18.018
Okay. Thank you.

30:41.842 --> 30:44.444
[ Whimpers ]

30:52.185 --> 30:56.356
<i>[ Chattering, Muffled ]</i>
<i>♪♪♪♪ [ Music, Muffled ]</i>

31:04.330 --> 31:06.499
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]
Mmm, mmm.

31:06.567 --> 31:10.737
Hold on. Hold on.
I think that could my brother.

31:10.804 --> 31:14.908
Is it him?
No. No, it's my mom.

31:14.975 --> 31:17.878
You‐‐ You don't want to‐‐

31:17.944 --> 31:20.246
No. No.

31:20.313 --> 31:22.616
[ Sniffles ]

31:30.824 --> 31:32.759
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>Yeah?</i>

31:32.826 --> 31:34.961
Gimme the works.
Okay.

31:43.504 --> 31:45.238
Is this your first time?

31:53.747 --> 31:58.484
[ Sighs ]
Yeah.

31:58.552 --> 32:01.087
Yeah, me too.

32:01.154 --> 32:04.124
[ Chattering, Music Continue ]
[ Sniffles ]

32:45.532 --> 32:48.168
[ Cries ]
Oh!

32:49.402 --> 32:53.039
Go on. You do it.
Do it.

32:53.106 --> 32:56.577
[ Woman ]
Hey, where you goin', babe?
<i>Hey.</i>

33:01.748 --> 33:05.586
Hey. You left this
on the grass at school today.

33:36.182 --> 33:38.619
[ Chattering ]

33:39.820 --> 33:42.523
Oh, shit.

33:42.589 --> 33:44.090
Oh!

33:46.560 --> 33:49.763
Shit. God.

33:51.532 --> 33:55.235
Dahlia, what the hell?
Hey. I know I shouldn't
have come here.

33:55.301 --> 33:59.439
You washed your hands of me,
and you're right. It's crazy.
What are you doin' here?

33:59.506 --> 34:02.142
Well, clearly,
I'm out of my mind, ain't I?

34:02.208 --> 34:05.746
I want to help you. I do.
Fifteen or 20 unanswered phone
calls is not real helpful.

34:05.812 --> 34:08.915
You're a parole officer.
You just don't get it, do you?

34:08.982 --> 34:10.784
What am I supposed to get?

34:14.955 --> 34:18.592
I didn't come here‐‐
I did not come here for that.
I'm sorry. Look, you know what?

34:18.659 --> 34:22.563
I didn't. I came here‐‐
I came here to talk to you.

34:22.629 --> 34:27.768
Your family's 20 feet away.
Forget it. I can't do that too.

34:27.833 --> 34:30.103
Dahlia!
[ Car Starts ]

34:30.170 --> 34:33.139
[ Tires Squeal ]

34:37.409 --> 34:40.681
Did you take my pot?
Well, uh, yes.

34:40.746 --> 34:43.583
Yeah. Uh, yes, I did.
Give it to me.
Give it to me.

34:43.650 --> 34:45.552
Here.

34:46.620 --> 34:49.422
[ Coughs, Sniffs ]
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

34:51.056 --> 34:53.694
<i>Nina, Wes.</i>

34:55.161 --> 34:56.530
Dr. Morgenstern.

34:56.597 --> 34:59.766
He brought you over
some food from the wake.

34:59.833 --> 35:02.135
‐ Thank you.
‐ Uh‐‐

35:02.202 --> 35:06.106
‐ Seen the kids?
‐ I think Sam is upstairs.
Don't know where Di Di is.

35:06.172 --> 35:08.308
‐ Chicken hero, Doug?
‐ No, thank you, Wes.

35:09.275 --> 35:12.579
Nina, do you know
where Cherien is?

35:13.747 --> 35:16.149
Where did you two go
after the funeral?

35:16.216 --> 35:20.486
[ Coughing ]

35:20.554 --> 35:22.623
Nowhere.

35:22.689 --> 35:25.358
A walk.

35:25.425 --> 35:27.894
‐ Why?
‐ You know where she is now?

35:27.961 --> 35:30.430
Mm‐mmm.
Sorry.

35:30.496 --> 35:33.366
Are you sure you don't know
where she is?

35:33.433 --> 35:36.937
I've been calling her all day.
Maybe you could call her.

35:37.003 --> 35:39.205
Me?

35:39.272 --> 35:41.875
‐ I really need to talk to her.
‐ <i>[ Dr. Morgenstern Muttering ]</i>

35:41.942 --> 35:45.979
Let me ask you this, Wayne.
Who is it you need so badly,

35:46.046 --> 35:49.215
Dahlia Malloy or Cherien Rich?

35:55.221 --> 35:57.991
Dahlia.
You sure?

35:58.058 --> 36:00.861
'Cause from where I'm sittin',

36:00.927 --> 36:03.630
you look to be
a little confused about that.

36:05.999 --> 36:07.768
Uh‐‐

36:18.244 --> 36:19.646
[ Coughing ]

36:19.713 --> 36:21.447
Yeah. Good shit.

36:21.515 --> 36:25.251
Uh‐huh.
Bobby McGee.

36:27.954 --> 36:29.923
Huh?

36:33.259 --> 36:36.196
These folks
just got this bed.
Hmm?

36:37.564 --> 36:40.233
Had it flown in
from France.

36:40.300 --> 36:43.704
Used to, like, belong to
an emperor or something.

36:47.608 --> 36:49.743
Well, it is
kinda like a cloud.

36:52.746 --> 36:55.682
I think
the Leadership Council
would have to approve.

36:57.283 --> 36:59.553
Leadership Council?

36:59.620 --> 37:03.323
Oh, yeah.
I'm a member of
the Celibacy Club, by the way.

37:06.793 --> 37:08.261
[ Chuckles ]

37:08.328 --> 37:10.463
Are you kidding?
Nope.

37:10.531 --> 37:12.065
Oh, my God.
Zero Alpha One. Over.

37:12.132 --> 37:14.535
Oh!
Jesus!

37:14.601 --> 37:17.137
Yeah.
Yeah, go ahead, Dad.

37:17.203 --> 37:20.140
Zero. Send. Over.

37:20.206 --> 37:24.678
‐ Status report. Over.
‐ Zero.
All sectors all clear. Over.

37:24.745 --> 37:27.581
Roger. Out.

37:27.648 --> 37:30.050
[ Sighs ]
You work for your dad?

37:30.116 --> 37:32.385
♪♪ I nailed it to your door ♪♪

37:32.452 --> 37:36.156
♪♪ It's crazy
how it all turned out ♪♪

37:36.222 --> 37:39.459
♪♪ You needed so much more ♪♪

37:39.526 --> 37:43.597
Your dad's a dick too, huh?

37:47.133 --> 37:49.703
[ Giggling ]

37:53.206 --> 37:56.610
Come on.
You look beautiful.
Really?

38:01.147 --> 38:03.283
Wait. Wait.

38:07.187 --> 38:10.023
♪♪ Please understand me ♪♪

38:10.090 --> 38:13.426
♪♪ My walls came falling down ♪♪

38:13.493 --> 38:16.863
♪♪ There's nothing here
that's left for you ♪♪

38:16.930 --> 38:21.001
♪♪ But check with
Lost and Found ♪♪

38:23.570 --> 38:26.707
<i>My dad's become a buffer.</i>

38:26.773 --> 38:29.042
There's nothin' more to say.
<i>Oh.</i>

38:29.109 --> 38:32.713
I happen to know that your da
is anything but a buffer,

38:32.779 --> 38:36.550
notwithstanding
